rComments: Professor Gourlay clearly has good intentions, though she is unable to deliver any dynamism through her lectures - they are very flat, long and monotone which makes it difficult to stay engaged. Honestly, most of the time it felt as though she didn't write her powerpoints and we were discovering it all together for the first time.

Miss three classes and fail??? Incredibly rude in emails. Doesn't give expectations on papers and gives very little feedback to go off of. This could be an interesting class but her lectures are so dull. Her grading is also super inconsistent. Avoid!
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Participation matters', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: She literally took at least 1 month before giving us our assignment back. Why would you ask for a 10page paper to write every 3 weeks if you can't mark them in time?!?! Didn't give us a lot of feedback on them so it's really hard to improve your grade. Also quite a tough grader... Would NOT recommend!

prof is super inconsistent with grading and seems to have a very specific idea of what they want but does not translate this to students. changes deadlines for tests as late as 2 days in advance. she's incredibly unorganized and unable to work efficiently with the online structure, really disappointing after being online for well over a year now

Very unorganized and does not grade fairly. She won't give you an upfront answer on anything regarding the school work she gives and if she does, she'll backtrack a few classes later. Avoid the class if you don't want an unnecessary headache.

avoid if possible. can only skip 3 classes or else you fail, class discussions and breakout rooms almost every class, and you have to "actively participate" in the online lectures even though they're recorded and participation isn't part of the grade. assignments arent bad but readings and lectures are very long and boring.

Just started this semester with this teacher but I already dont like her. She is awful, she always wants you to participate. Im a shy person so I dont like to participate so the fact that she forces us to and it counts towards our grades increases my level of anxiety. If you miss more than 4 classes you automatically fail. Update once finish.
